    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571163",
        "quote": "Mushrooms provide a vast array of potential medicinal compounds. Many mushrooms - such as portobello, oyster, reishi and maitake - are well-known for these properties, but the lion's mane mushroom, in particular, has drawn the attention of researchers for its notable nerve-regenerative properties.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571163"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Notable",
                "url": "/topics/notable"
            },
            {
                "name": "Medicinal",
                "url": "/topics/medicinal"
            },
            {
                "name": "Array",
                "url": "/topics/array"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571137",
        "quote": "Mushrooms have many helpful nutrients, including beta glucans for immune enhancement, ergothioneines for antioxidative potentiation, nerve growth stimulators for helping brain function, and antimicrobial compounds for limiting viruses.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571137"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Including",
                "url": "/topics/including"
            },
            {
                "name": "Viruses",
                "url": "/topics/viruses"
            },
            {
                "name": "Immune",
                "url": "/topics/immune"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571127",
        "quote": "Mushrooms are miniature pharmaceutical factories, and of the thousands of mushroom species in nature, our ancestors and modern scientists have identified several dozen that have a unique combination of talents that improve our health.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571127"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Nature",
                "url": "/topics/nature"
            },
            {
                "name": "Pharmaceutical",
                "url": "/topics/pharmaceutical"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571129",
        "quote": "Fungi are the grand recyclers of the planet and the vanguard species in habitat restoration.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571129"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Planet",
                "url": "/topics/planet"
            },
            {
                "name": "Habitat",
                "url": "/topics/habitat"
            },
            {
                "name": "Species",
                "url": "/topics/species"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571162",
        "quote": "Disasters such as earthquakes, tsunamis, volcanoes, floods, oil spills and radioactive fallout cause massive death of people, pigs, bats and birds. These disasters also impact the immune health of survivors. All harbor viruses.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571162"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Death",
                "url": "/topics/death"
            },
            {
                "name": "Floods",
                "url": "/topics/floods"
            },
            {
                "name": "Radioactive",
                "url": "/topics/radioactive"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571147",
        "quote": "Maitake mushrooms are known in Japan as 'the dancing mushroom.' According to a Japanese legend, a group of Buddhist nuns and woodcutters met on a mountain trail, where they discovered a fruiting of maitake mushrooms emerging from the forest floor. Rejoicing at their discovery of this delicious mushroom, they danced to celebrate.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571147"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Forest",
                "url": "/topics/forest"
            },
            {
                "name": "Dancing",
                "url": "/topics/dancing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Discovered",
                "url": "/topics/discovered"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571135",
        "quote": "If you do not know where the mushroom products you are consuming are grown, think twice before eating them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571135"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            },
            {
                "name": "Them",
                "url": "/topics/them"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571126",
        "quote": "Nature is a numbers game. We need all the support we can get as our immune systems and health are under assault from pollution, stress, contaminated food and age-related diseases as our lifespans increase.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571126"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Game",
                "url": "/topics/game"
            },
            {
                "name": "Assault",
                "url": "/topics/assault"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571136",
        "quote": "The virus-to-cancer connection is where medicinal mushrooms offer unique opportunities for medical research.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571136"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Mushrooms",
                "url": "/topics/mushrooms"
            },
            {
                "name": "Offer",
                "url": "/topics/offer"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571152",
        "quote": "Through trial-and-error and observable outcomes, our ancestors narrowed the field of edible mushroom candidates to just a few with remarkable, health-supporting properties.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571152"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Remarkable",
                "url": "/topics/remarkable"
            },
            {
                "name": "Our",
                "url": "/topics/our"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571134",
        "quote": "Traditionally, our ancestors boiled mushrooms in water to make a soothing tea. Boiling served several purposes: killing contaminants, softening the flesh, and extracting the rich soluble polysaccharides.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571134"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Rich",
                "url": "/topics/rich"
            },
            {
                "name": "Soothing",
                "url": "/topics/soothing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Several",
                "url": "/topics/several"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571143",
        "quote": "In the wild, an enoki mushroom is often squat-looking and its stem is rarely more than twice as long as the cap is wide. When they are grown by farmers and hobbyists, however, their stems elongate, the caps are smaller, and a forest of golden colored needle-like mushrooms shoot up all at once.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571143"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stems",
                "url": "/topics/stems"
            },
            {
                "name": "However",
                "url": "/topics/however"
            },
            {
                "name": "Smaller",
                "url": "/topics/smaller"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571130",
        "quote": "Some people think I'm a mycological heretic, some people think I'm a mycological revolutionary, and some just think I'm crazy.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571130"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Revolutionary",
                "url": "/topics/revolutionary"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571142",
        "quote": "Known colloquially as 'winter,' 'golden needle,' and 'velvet foot' mushrooms, enoki mushrooms grow across much of the world, inhabiting dead conifer trees and stumps, and generally appearing throughout the late fall and winter months.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571142"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Grow",
                "url": "/topics/grow"
            },
            {
                "name": "Months",
                "url": "/topics/months"
            },
            {
                "name": "Inhabiting",
                "url": "/topics/inhabiting"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571150",
        "quote": "Although oyster mushrooms have been studied extensively and support health in a number of ways, it is also extremely important to always cook oyster mushrooms!",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571150"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Studied",
                "url": "/topics/studied"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571131",
        "quote": "If you look on the fungal genome as being soldier candidates protecting the U.S. as our host defense, not only for the ecosystem but for our population... we should be saving our old-growth forests as a matter of national defense.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571131"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Being",
                "url": "/topics/being"
            },
            {
                "name": "Protecting",
                "url": "/topics/protecting"
            },
            {
                "name": "Ecosystem",
                "url": "/topics/ecosystem"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571151",
        "quote": "While reishi mushrooms have historically been prepared as teas or infusions, other modern preparations include capsules, tinctures, and fractionated extracts of mushrooms, mycelium, and spores.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571151"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
