            },
            {
                "name": "Include",
                "url": "/topics/include"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571156",
        "quote": "Growing the mycelium of the Chaga mushroom under laboratory conditions provides an ecologically friendly alternative supply of this unique medicinal mushroom.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571156"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Friendly",
                "url": "/topics/friendly"
            },
            {
                "name": "Alternative",
                "url": "/topics/alternative"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571139",
        "quote": "We evolved living in more sunlight than today. We make our own vitamin D when sunlight hits our skin cells. Many people living in the northern hemisphere, however, suffer from lower levels of vitamin D during the fall, winter and spring.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571139"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "However",
                "url": "/topics/however"
            },
            {
                "name": "Evolved",
                "url": "/topics/evolved"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571145",
        "quote": "My family is delighted every time I cook maitake. Our taste buds awaken in anticipation of its rich, deep and nuanced flavors.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571145"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Deep",
                "url": "/topics/deep"
            },
            {
                "name": "Cook",
                "url": "/topics/cook"
            },
            {
                "name": "Flavors",
                "url": "/topics/flavors"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571165",
        "quote": "Lion's mane may be our first 'smart' mushroom. It is a safe, edible fungus that appears to confer cognitive benefits on our aging population.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571165"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "May",
                "url": "/topics/may"
            },
            {
                "name": "Benefits",
                "url": "/topics/benefits"
            },
            {
                "name": "Appears",
                "url": "/topics/appears"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571138",
        "quote": "Vitamin D from mushrooms is not only vegan and vegetarian friendly, but you can prepare your own by exposing mushrooms to the summer sun.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571138"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Prepare",
                "url": "/topics/prepare"
            },
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "Friendly",
                "url": "/topics/friendly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571153",
        "quote": "Today, reishi stands out as one the most valuable of all polypore mushrooms in nature for the benefit of our health. Many naturopaths and doctors prefer organically-grown reishi from pristine environments because they are more pure.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571153"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Pure",
                "url": "/topics/pure"
            },
            {
                "name": "Prefer",
                "url": "/topics/prefer"
            },
            {
                "name": "Environments",
                "url": "/topics/environments"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571159",
        "quote": "The majority of modern medicines originate in nature. Although some mushrooms have been used in therapies for thousands of years, we are still discovering new potential medicines hidden within them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571159"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571128",
        "quote": "My team and I have discovered, over decades of study, that mushroom mycelium is a rich resource of new antimicrobial compounds, which work in concert, helping protecting the mushrooms - and us - from microbial pathogens.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571128"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Over",
                "url": "/topics/over"
            },
            {
                "name": "Protecting",
                "url": "/topics/protecting"
            },
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571148",
        "quote": "Of all mushrooms commonly consumed, oyster mushrooms in the genus Pleurotus stand out as exceptional allies for improving human and environmental health. These mushrooms enjoy a terrific reputation as the easiest to cultivate, richly nutritious and medicinally supportive.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571148"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Enjoy",
                "url": "/topics/enjoy"
            },
            {
                "name": "Supportive",
                "url": "/topics/supportive"
            },
            {
                "name": "Consumed",
                "url": "/topics/consumed"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571125",
        "quote": "Mycologists are few and far between. We are under-funded, poorly represented in the context of other sciences - ironic, as the very foundation of our ecosystems are directly dependent upon fungi, which ultimately create the foundation of soils.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571125"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Which",
                "url": "/topics/which"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Poorly",
                "url": "/topics/poorly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571132",
        "quote": "Life exists throughout the cosmos and is a consequence of matter in the universe.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571132"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Universe",
                "url": "/topics/universe"
            },
            {
                "name": "Consequence",
                "url": "/topics/consequence"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571133",
        "quote": "Turkey tail mushrooms have been used to treat various maladies for hundreds of years in Asia, Europe, and by indigenous peoples in North America. Records of turkey tail brewed as medicinal tea date from the early 15th century, during the Ming Dynasty in China.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571133"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Treat",
                "url": "/topics/treat"
            },
            {
                "name": "Date",
                "url": "/topics/date"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571140",
        "quote": "Enoki mushrooms, a tasty variety commonly sold in grocery stores, were one of the first mushrooms studied for preventing cancer.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571140"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Sold",
                "url": "/topics/sold"
            },
            {
                "name": "Commonly",
                "url": "/topics/commonly"
            },
            {
                "name": "Preventing",
                "url": "/topics/preventing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571141",
        "quote": "Nitric oxide production by immune cells is one of the key mechanisms that our bodies use to destroy diseased cells. Enhancement of these types of immune responses is seen consistently with many medicinal mushrooms that have been tested by cancer researchers.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571141"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Production",
                "url": "/topics/production"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Bodies",
                "url": "/topics/bodies"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571144",
        "quote": "Maitake can achieve humongous sizes, sometimes up to 50 pounds per specimen! Massive maitake can form annually from dying dendritic tree roots for many years, even decades.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571144"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Tree",
                "url": "/topics/tree"
            },
            {
                "name": "Sometimes",
                "url": "/topics/sometimes"
            },
            {
                "name": "Achieve",
                "url": "/topics/achieve"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571146",
        "quote": "In the past, mushrooms were maligned as nutritionally poor. Since they are about 80 to 90 percent water when fresh, their net concentrations of nutrients can be underestimated. Like grains, however, mushrooms should be weighed when dry to get their correct nutrient value.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571146"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            },
            {
                "name": "Correct",
                "url": "/topics/correct"
            },
            {
                "name": "However",
                "url": "/topics/however"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571154",
        "quote": "Although the trends are promising and reishi mushrooms exhibit a number of interesting medicinal properties, modern scientific techniques have yet to affirm its traditional 'panacea polypore' status.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571154"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Interesting",
                "url": "/topics/interesting"
            },
            {
                "name": "Panacea",
                "url": "/topics/panacea"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571155",
        "quote": "Chaga is one of the weirdest mushrooms you may ever see. A fungal parasite found on birch trees, Chaga is a hardened, blackened, crusty formation that looks like a bursting tumor.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571155"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "May",
                "url": "/topics/may"
            },
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            },
            {
                "name": "Birch",
                "url": "/topics/birch"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571157",
        "quote": "Chaga mycelium is relatively easy to grow by using methods already practiced elsewhere in the mushroom industry. Its mycelium is initially an off-whitish color, deepening with age.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Paul Stamets",
            "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571157"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Color",
                "url": "/topics/color"
            },
            {
                "name": "Grow",
                "url": "/topics/grow"
            },
            {
                "name": "Using",
                "url": "/topics/using"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/paul_stamets_571158",
        "quote": "Chaga is significant in ethnomycology, forest ecology, and increasingly in pharmacognosy. Its long-term human use and cultural eastern European and Russian acceptance should awaken serious researchers to its potential as a reservoir of new medicines, and as a powerful preventive ally for protecting DNA.",
